{
  "texts": [
    "However, LoRA-based fine-tuning incurs only onethird of the communication overhead required by methods involving extra adapters.",
    "SLoRA [50] introduced an optimization of LoRA tailored for non-IID FL settings.",
    "It employs a ratio to moderate the influence of updates from individual clients, aiming to counteract the drift caused by heterogeneous data distributions.",
    "Although it reportedly matches the performance of full model fine-tuning, it requires a considerable warm-up period to ensure that all clients share a common initialization of LoRA.",
    "pFedLoRA [88] first introduced LoRA into model-heterogeneous FL."
  ]
}